\title{educabr2: Harmonized Historical Series on Brazilian Education}
\description{
Curated long-run series on Brazilian formal education — enrollment and
educational attainment — compiled from heterogeneous official and
academic sources into a single tidy schema with explicit provenance.
}
\details{
The canonical output schema (one row per observation; sources as
separate rows) is documented in \code{inst/dict/schema.yaml}. Inequality is
not a dataset but a \emph{cut} applied to indicators: every \verb{get_*()}
function accepts a \code{dimension} argument that returns the indicator
broken down by race, sex, income or location. A \code{compute_gap()}
helper for turning long-format breakdowns into the usual gap/ratio
metrics is on the roadmap for a future release.
}
\section{Roadmap}{

v0 lays out the data schema, ETL pipeline and package skeleton. The
first user-facing functions — \code{get_enrollment()} and \code{get_schooling()}
— and the bundled Shiny dashboard (\code{run_dashboard()}) are scheduled
for the v0.2–v0.4 milestones. See \code{NEWS.md} once released.
}

